The paper discusses a new architecture for wireless networks, specifically for lower tiers in the hierarchy, which involves the use of remote radio heads (RRHs) to provide high-capacity wireless infrastructure. The paper also proposes a novel coded pilot contamination control mechanism to mitigate pilot contamination. These topics are closely related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and augmented reality (cs.AR).
